The paper deals with object detection using convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The specific application of the object detection is for autonomous humanoid robots playing soccer, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also proposes an adaptation to the YOLO CNN model, which involves machine learning techniques and falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the trade-off between accuracy and speed, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper achieves greater inference speed-ups on a desktop CPU and GPU, which falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
